==Description== 

The [[Image:Sketcher_CreateText.svg|24px]] [[Sketcher_CreateText|Sketcher CreateText]] tool creates text geometries controlled by a Text constraint.

==Usage==

See also: [[Sketcher_Workbench#Drawing_aids|Drawing aids]].

Pos-OVP = Positional [[Sketcher_Preferences#General|On-View-Parameters]]. {{Version|1.0}}

# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Sketcher_CreateText.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_CreateText|Text]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Sketch → Geometries → [[Image:Sketcher_CreateText.svg|16px]] Text}} option from the menu.
#* Right-click in the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_CreateText.svg|16px]] Text}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|G}} then {{KEY|T}}.
# The cursor changes to a cross with the tool icon.
# The '''Text Parameters''' section is added at the top of the [[Sketcher_Dialog|Sketcher Dialog]].
# Optionally press the {{KEY|M}} key or select from the dropdown list in the parameters section to change the tool mode:
#* '''Width''':
#*# Optionally select a different '''Font''' from the dropdown list.
#*# Optionally enter a '''Text'''t.
#*# Pick a start point. Or with Pos-OVP: enter its X- and/or Y-coordinate.
#*# Pick an end point. Or with Pos-OVP: enter the length and/or angle of the text.
#* '''Height''':
#*# Optionally select a different '''Font''' from the dropdown list.
#*# Optionally enter a '''Text'''.
#*# Pick a start point (bottom). Or with Pos-OVP: enter its X- and/or Y-coordinate.
#*# Pick an end point (top). Or with Pos-OVP: enter the height and/or angle of the text.
# The text, a '''Text''' object, is created and applicable Pos-OVP based constraints are added.
# If the tool runs in [[Sketcher_Workbench#Continue_modes|continue mode]]:
## Optionally keep creating texts.
## To finish, right-click or press {{KEY|Esc}}, or start another geometry or constraint creation tool.

==Notes== 

* In the initial version the Pos-OVP entry field related to the y-coordinate only accepts a single digit.


